text: Arabica may refer to: * Coffea arabica, a coffee tree species * Arebica or Arabica, the Bosnian Arabic alphabet * The Belarusian Arabic alphabet * Arabica (journal), a journal of Arabic and Islamic studies and also * Revalenta arabica, a preparation which was sold in the 18th century as an empirical diet for invalids, extraordinary restorative virtues being attributed to it ==Genera / Species / subspecies == * Arabica (genus), an extant animal genus represented in the fossil record * Vulpes vulpes arabica, the Arabian red fox, a red fox subspecies native to Arabia
title: Arabica
